column5: I AM LOOKING FOR A GOOD WALLEYE FISHING RESORT FOR MYSELF AND MY WIFE IN CENTRAL OR NORTHERN ONTARIO.WE HAVE BEEN GOING TO LAC SEUL BUT THE COST OF GAS IS GETTING RIDICULOUS. I WAS LOOKING FOR RECOMMENDATIONS OF PLACES NORTH OF NIPISSING.

I AM LOOKING FOR A GOOD WALLEYE FISHING RESORT FOR MYSELF AND MY WIFE IN CENTRAL OR NORTHERN ONTARIO.WE HAVE BEEN GOING TO LAC SEUL BUT THE COST OF GAS IS GETTING RIDICULOUS. I WAS LOOKING FOR RECOMMENDATIONS OF PLACES NORTH OF NIPISSING.
Its not north of Nippissing, actual west, but I'd recommend the French River Lodge on the Lower French River. John

Nice area to visit but it was fished out years ago. Night fishing the first 2 weeks of June with big floating raplalas is your best bet for wallhangers because fishing in the daytime won't get you dog squat.
